
Google has several official help communities for most of its services, such as Gmail, Youtube, Blogger etc. A Google Help Forum is a community of general users, who enjoy helping each other figure out the best ways to use a product.[tpl]cite web|title=Google Help Forums|url=http://support.google.com/bin/static.py?hl=en&page=portal_groups.cs|publisher=Google|accessdate=27 February 2012[/tpl]

==History==

Google started their user to user help communities named Google discussion groups in 2005 in Google Groups platform. In 2009, many of the official Google discussion groups moved from Google Groups to a new platform called "Google Help Forums".  [tpl]cite web|title=Google Help Forums Migrate to Google Groups|url=http://googlesystem.blogspot.in/2011/11/google-help-forums-migrate-to-google.html|publisher=Google Operating System Unofficial news and tips about Google|accessdate=27 February 2012[/tpl] From the end of 2011 Google started to move back to Google Groups again.[tpl]cite web|title=Weâ€™re moving to Google Product Forums!|url=http://www.google.com/support/forum/p/base/thread?tid=4260f1de0b532fcb&hl=en|publisher=Google|accessdate=27 February 2012|author=Nickkie[/tpl] Google Analytics team posted in their blog post that the new Google product forums offer more stability and more features.[tpl]cite web|title=A new forum for Google Analytics using Google Product Forums|url=http://analytics.blogspot.in/2012/01/new-forum-for-google-analytics-using.html|publisher=Google|accessdate=27 February 2012|author=Aruna, Community Manager - Google Analytics[/tpl]

==Community structure==

Google Help Forums are mainly user to user platform where users ask questions and other users provide answers of those questions. Google claims, occasionally, Google employees participate in Google Help Forums.[tpl]cite web|title=Getting Started with Google Help Forums  - About|url=http://support.google.com/faqs/bin/static.py?hl=en&topic=19835&guide=19559&page=guide.cs|publisher=Google|accessdate=27 February 2012[/tpl] Besides official Google blogs, Google sometimes use Google Help Forums for important announcements. Anyone can join these forums and post questions and answers.[tpl]cite web|title=Joining Google Help Forums|url=http://support.google.com/faqs/bin/static.py?hl=en&topic=19561&guide=19559&page=guide.cs|publisher=Google|accessdate=27 February 2012[/tpl]
;Top Contributors
The most helpful and regular users of the community are selected as Top Contributors.[tpl]cite web|title=Levels and Points.|url=http://support.google.com/faqs/bin/static.py?hl=en&topic=19565&guide=19559&page=guide.cs|publisher=Google|accessdate=27 February 2012[/tpl][tpl]cite web|title=Faces of Gmail Top Contributors|url=http://gmailblog.blogspot.com/2011/10/faces-of-gmail-forum-top-contributors.html|publisher=Gmail Team - Google|accessdate=27 February 2012[/tpl]
*On September 13-14, 2011, Google organized their first global Top Contributors' summit which was held in Santa Clara Marriott and Google Headquarters, Mountain View.[tpl]cite web|title=2011 Global Top Contributor Summit|url=http://www.google.com/events/tcsummit2011/|publisher=Google|accessdate=30 March 2012[/tpl]
*In March, 2012 Google started Google Top Contributor Program which consists of 470 members across more than 24 Google products and 50 countries.[tpl]cite web|title=Google Top Contributor Program About the Program|url=http://support.google.com/bin/static.py?hl=en&topic=2546991&guide=2518472&page=guide.cs&answer=2518474|publisher=Google|accessdate=30 March 2012[/tpl]
;Rising stars
Some help forums provide some other tags for regular and helpful users (eg. Rising Gmail Star in Gmail Help Forum, Blogger Addict in Blogger (service) Help Forum, Starred Users in Orkut Help Forum etc.[tpl]cite web|title=Rising Stars|url=http://support.google.com/bin/static.py?hl=en&topic=2546991&guide=2518472&page=guide.cs&answer=2523468|publisher=Google|accessdate=30 March 2012[/tpl]

